==History==
Ogawa Station opened on 21 December 1894.<ref name="terada2013"/>

Station numbering was introduced on all Seibu Railway lines during fiscal 2012, with Ogawa Station becoming "SS31" on the Haijima Line and "SK04" on the Kokubunji Line.<ref name="seibu20120223">{{cite web |url= http://www.seibu-group.co.jp/railways/news/news-release/2011/__icsFiles/afieldfile/2012/02/23/20110223eki-number.pdf|title= <U+897F><U+6B66><U+7DDA><U+5168><U+99C5><U+3067><U+99C5><U+30CA><U+30F3><U+30D0><U+30EA><U+30F3><U+30B0><U+3092><U+5C0E><U+5165><U+3057><U+307E><U+3059>|trans_title= Station numbering to be introduced at all Seibu stations|date= 23 February 2012|work= News Release|publisher= Seibu Railway|location= Japan|language= Japanese|format= pdf|archiveurl= |archivedate= |accessdate= 17 November 2013}}</ref>

==Passenger statistics==
In fiscal 2012, the station was used by an average of 28,550 passengers daily.<ref name="stats2012">{{cite web|url=http://www.seibu-group.co.jp/railways/company/business/railway-business/data/year/__icsFiles/afieldfile/2013/06/11/2012joukou.pdf|title=<U+99C5><U+5225><U+4E57><U+964D><U+4EBA><U+54E1><U+3000>(2012<U+5E74><U+5EA6>1<U+65E5><U+5E73><U+5747>)|trans_title=Average daily station usage figures (fiscal 2012)|language=Japanese|location = Japan |publisher=Seibu Railway|format=PDF|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref> The passenger figures for previous years are as shown below.

